    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\n`globals.h` exposes ~283 bare `EXTERN` symbols to every translation unit (~150 files). This makes subsystem ownership unclear, prevents unit-testing individual subsystems in isolation, and blocks future threading work.\r\n\r\nCloses #39481 (first incremental slice).\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nIntroduce `search_defs.h` with a `SearchState` struct that owns the 8 search/highlight globals previously declared as bare `EXTERN` symbols in `globals.h`:\r\n\r\n- `highlight_match`\r\n- `search_match_lines` / `search_match_endcol`\r\n- `search_first_line` / `search_last_line`\r\n- `no_smartcase`\r\n- `searchcmdlen`\r\n- `no_hlsearch`\r\n\r\n`globals.h` now declares a single `EXTERN SearchState search_state` in place of those 8 lines. All ~60 call sites across 16 files are updated to use `search_state.<field>`.\r\n\r\nThis is an opt-in, incremental migration — no function signatures are changed and no behavior is altered. The struct creates a named seam for future per-thread or parameter-threaded instantiation.\r\n",
